Assignment 1

Create bar or line charts showing monthly total kBTUs of residential and commercial electricity and gas consumption for the Bay Area (meaning the sum of all ZIP codes in the 9 Bay Area counties) from 2017 to the latest available month (meaning a 42-column version of the plots from section 1.8). Look online for the correct conversion of kWhs to kBTUs and therms to kBTUs. Make sure that electricity and gas data are distinguishable but plotted in the same chart; feel free to separate your analyses for residential and commercial into two separate charts if you believe it improves legibility, or do one chart with 4 colors in the legend.

Comment on any observable changes in energy consumption that may be attributable to the COVID-19 pandemic. Create at least one map that highlights which neighborhoods experienced the greatest change in electricity consumption before and after the pandemic began, and comment on your results. Explain any key assumptions you made in the analysis, or caveats about the data sources that you think the reader should be aware of. Publish all of this work in a web report

years <- 2017:2019

for (year in years){

    paste0(
      "PGE_",
      year,
      "_Q",
      quarter,
      "_",
      type,
      "UsageByZip.csv"
    )

  print(filename)
  
  temp <- read_csv(filename)
  
  pge_17_19_elec <- rbind(pge_17_19_elec,temp)
  # Note rbind requires field names to be consistent for every new thing that you add.

  saveRDS(pge_17_19_elec, "pge_17_19_elec.rds")
}}

get bay zipcodes

bay_zipcodes<-read_csv("bayarea_zipcodes.csv")

#DATA cleaning and organization, pge_final_elec

pge_final_elec <-
pge_elec %>% 
  filter(ZIPCODE %in% bay_zipcodes$ZIP) %>% 
  filter(CUSTOMERCLASS %in% c("Elec- Commercial", "Elec- Residential")) %>% 
  select(!c(COMBINED, AVERAGEKWH)) %>% 
  group_by(YEAR,MONTH, CUSTOMERCLASS) %>% 
  summarise(
    TOTALKWH = sum(TOTALKWH,na.rm = T),
    TOTALCUSTOMERS =sum(TOTALCUSTOMERS,na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    TOTALKBTU =
      TOTALKWH*3.412
  ) %>% 
  select(!c(TOTALKWH, TOTALCUSTOMERS))

pge_final_elec

#DATA cleaning and organization, pge_final_gas

pge_final_gas <-
pge_gas %>% 
  filter(ZIPCODE %in% bay_zipcodes$ZIP) %>% 
  filter(CUSTOMERCLASS %in% c("Gas- Commercial", "Gas- Residential")) %>% 
  select(!c(COMBINED, AVERAGETHM)) %>% 
  group_by(YEAR,MONTH, CUSTOMERCLASS) %>% 
  summarise(
    TOTALTHM = sum(TOTALTHM,na.rm = T),
    TOTALCUSTOMERS =sum(TOTALCUSTOMERS,na.rm = T)
  )%>% 
  mutate(
    TOTALKBTU =
      TOTALTHM*99.976
  ) %>% 
  select(!c(TOTALCUSTOMERS, TOTALTHM))

seperate commercial and residential, convert time

pge_final<-rbind(pge_final_elec,pge_final_gas)

pge_commerical<-
pge_final %>% filter(CUSTOMERCLASS %in% c("Elec- Commercial", "Gas- Commercial"))
pge_commerical$TIME <- with(pge_commerical, sprintf("%d-%02d", YEAR, MONTH))

pge_residential<-
pge_final %>% filter(CUSTOMERCLASS %in% c("Elec- Residential", "Gas- Residential"))
pge_residential$TIME <- with(pge_residential, sprintf("%d-%02d", YEAR, MONTH))

chart-plotting-commercial

pge_chart_commercial <-
  pge_commerical %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = TIME,
      y = TOTALKBTU,
      fill = CUSTOMERCLASS
    ),
    stat = "identity",
    position = "stack"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Time",
    y = "kBTU",
    title = "PG&E Monthly Commercial Gas and Electricity Usage in Bay Area, 2017-2020",
    fill = "Type"
  )+coord_flip()

pge_chart_commercial

Despite the seasonal changes, it could be observed that the commercial energy use did experienced a decrease, while the gas consumption experienced even a greater change, which can be attributed to the closures of a wide range of businesses. It also should be noted that PG&E only cover a portion of the bay area so should not be used to reflect the situation of the entire bay area. For the purpose of this assignment, it is assumed that through the length of the record period, the households/area that PG&E supplies remain the same, as well as the way of recording the energy usage.

#calculate the avg for each zipcode in 17-19
  pge_17_19_tot <-
  pge_17_19_elec %>% 
  filter(ZIPCODE %in% bay_zipcodes$ZIP) %>% 
  select(!c(COMBINED, AVERAGEKWH,CUSTOMERCLASS)) %>% 
  group_by(ZIPCODE)%>% 
  summarise(
    TOTALKWH = sum(TOTALKWH,na.rm = T),
    TOTALCUSTOMERS =sum(TOTALCUSTOMERS,na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
mutate(
    AVGKWH_before =
      TOTALKWH/TOTALCUSTOMERS) %>% 
  select(!c(TOTALKWH,TOTALCUSTOMERS))

#calculate the avg for each zipcode in 20
  pge_20_tot <-
  pge_20_elec %>% 
  filter(ZIPCODE %in% bay_zipcodes$ZIP) %>% 
  select(!c(COMBINED, AVERAGEKWH,CUSTOMERCLASS)) %>% 
  group_by(ZIPCODE)%>% 
  summarise(
    TOTALKWH = sum(TOTALKWH,na.rm = T),
    TOTALCUSTOMERS =sum(TOTALCUSTOMERS,na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
mutate(
    AVGKWH_after =
      TOTALKWH/TOTALCUSTOMERS) %>% 
      select(!c(TOTALKWH,TOTALCUSTOMERS))
  
#merge two df

ca_counties_transformed <- 
  ca_counties %>% 
  st_transform(projection) 

bay_county_names <-
  c(

    "Marin",
    "Napa",
    "San Francisco",
    "San Mateo",
    "Santa Clara",
    "Solano",
    "Sonoma"
  )

bay_counties <-
  counties("CA", cb = T, progress_bar = F) %>%
  filter(NAME %in% bay_county_names)

decrese_t<-c("94105","94104","95134")
increase_t<-c("94111","94533","94545")

usa_zips <- 
  zctas(cb = T, progress_bar = F)

bay_zips <-
  usa_zips %>% 
  st_centroid() %>% 
  .[bay_counties, ] %>% 
  st_set_geometry(NULL) %>% 
  left_join(usa_zips %>% select(GEOID10)) %>% 
  st_as_sf()
total_map1 <-
  total_bf %>% 
  mutate(
    ZIPCODE = ZIPCODE %>% as.character()
  ) %>% 
  right_join(
    bay_zips %>% select(GEOID10),
    by = c("ZIPCODE" = "GEOID10")
  ) %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% 
  st_transform(4326)

total_map<-filter(total_map1, DIFF!="NaN"& DIFF!= "NA")
res_pal <- colorNumeric(
  palette = "Blues",
  domain = total_map$DIFF
)

leaflet() %>% 
  addTiles() %>% 
  addPolygons(
    data = total_map,
    fillColor = ~res_pal(DIFF),
    color = "white",
    opacity = 0.1,
    fillOpacity = 0.5,
    weight = 1,
    label = ~paste0(
      round(DIFF), 
      " kWh difference in",
      ZIPCODE
    ),
    highlightOptions = highlightOptions(
      weight = 2,
      opacity = 1
    ))%>% 
    addPolygons(
    data = total_map %>% 
      filter(ZIPCODE %in% decrese_t) %>% 
      st_transform(4326),
    color = "red") %>% 
   addPolygons(
    data = total_map %>% 
      filter(ZIPCODE %in% increase_t) %>% 
      st_transform(4326),
    color = "green") %>% 
  addLegend(
    data = total_map,
    pal = res_pal,
    values = ~DIFF,
    title = "Difference in Total Elec Usage Pre/Post- Covid-19")

Due to the outliers in the difference in electricity use, the color coding was not very informative in this case. Therefore, the areas with the greatest increase and decrease are marked here in the map using green and red, respectively. It was then found that the changes in energy use varies considerably regrading the location, which can be potentially due to the different uses of land.
